ETHICAL USE ADDENDUM

This addendum does not alter or restrict the permissions granted by the MIT
License above. It serves as a statement of intent and a call to conscience for
all users of this software.

1. Intended Purpose
   This software was designed to support legitimate activities including
   independent security research, investigative journalism, academic study,
   and educational demonstration of open-source intelligence techniques.
   Users are encouraged to apply it in ways that contribute positively to
   society and the public interest.

2. Legal Compliance
   Every user bears full responsibility for ensuring their use of this
   software complies with all applicable laws, regulations, and jurisdictional
   requirements in their location and in the locations of any individuals or
   entities they investigate. Ignorance of local law is not a defense.

3. Prohibition on Harmful Use
   This software must not be used to harass, intimidate, stalk, threaten, or
   cause harm to any individual or group. It must not be weaponized against
   activists, journalists, whistleblowers, or any person exercising lawful
   rights. Any use that enables discrimination, targeted violence, or
   coordinated abuse is strictly contrary to the spirit of this project.

4. Respect for Privacy
   Open-source information is not a license for intrusion. Users are expected
   to exercise judgment and restraint, recognizing that the availability of
   data does not automatically justify its collection, aggregation, or
   publication. The dignity and safety of individuals must remain a primary
   consideration in every use case.

5. Disclaimer of Responsibility for Misuse
   The authors and copyright holders of this software explicitly disclaim any
   responsibility for harm arising from misuse, abuse, or negligent application
   of this tool. By using this software, you accept sole accountability for
   the consequences of your actions.
